ing by a Missile-like Body with a Surface Impedance Boundary Conditio n&#8221;, <cite>ICEAA&#8217;93</cite>, Turin, Italy, September 1993.</li><li>P.L.E. Uslenghi, &#8220;Exact Radiation and Scattering from an Oblate Spheroidal Cavity in a Ground Plane&#8221;, <cite>National Radio Science Meeting</cite>, Bould er, Colorado, January 1994.</li><li>P.L.E. Uslenghi and H.-Y. Yang, &#8220;An Inverse Method for Scattering from Anisotropic Objects in Generalized Anisotropic Grounded Layers&#8221;,<cite>Proceedings of Unexploded Ordnance</cite> <cite>(UXO) Detection and Ran ge Remediation Conference</cite>, pp. 61-82, Golden, Colorado, May 1994.</li><li>S.O. Brauer, R.L. Kustom and P.L.E. Uslenghi, &#8220;Field Configuration of Beam Excited Modes in the Advanced Photon Source Storage Ring Waveguides&#8221;, <cite>Proceedings of the International</cite> <cite>Symposium on Electromagne tic Environments and Consequences</cite>, Bordeaux, France, June 1994.</li><li>H.-Y. Yang and P.L.E. Uslenghi, &#8220;A Numerical Method of Evaluating Electromagnetic Fields in Multi-layer Generalized Anisotropic Media&#8221;, <cite>1 994 IEEE-APS/URSI International</cite> <cite></cite><cite>Symposium</cite>, Seattle, Washington, June 1994.</li><li>R.D. Graglia, P.L.E. Uslenghi, U.F. D&#8217;Elia and R. Vitiello, &#8220;Transient Scattering by Conductive and Resistive Bodies of Revolution&#8221;, <cite>1994 IEEE-APS/URSI International</cite> <cite>Symposium</cite>, Seattle , Washington, June 1994.</li><li>S.F. Kawalko, S.R. Laxpati and P.L.E. Uslenghi, &#8220;Co-pol and Cross-pol Radar Cross Sections for a Missile-like Body with an Impedance Patch&#8221;,<cite>1994 IEEE-APS/URSI </cite><cite>International Symposium</cite>, Seattle, Washington, June 1994.</li><li>P. Soudais and P.L.E. Uslenghi, &#8220;Modification of the Integral Equations for Smooth Conducting Objects using Fock Functions&#8221;, <cite>1994 IEEE-APS/UR SI International Symposium</cite>, Seattle, Washington, June 1994.</li><li>T